      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness under compression-bending is the primary QoI for pre-market assessment of posterior spinal fixation devices. This QoI is directly linked to the clinical performance endpoint of fatigue life and subsidence risk, consistent with FDA guidance on spinal implant submissions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Validation activity replicates the ASTM F1717 test configuration used in the regulatory submission. Component geometry, material, and assembly match the device design intended for clearance. Validation evidence is therefore directly relevant to the intended use context, though the structured context of use specification is not formalized in this minimal-profile package."
